---

## How it works

  Browser → React app → /api/fixtures (your server) → API-Football → back to user

  Your server runs 24/7, fetches from API-Football server-to-server (no CORS),
  caches results for 30 seconds (saves API calls), and serves everything to users.

  User accounts are stored in a SQLite database file (betplay.db) on the server.
  Bets, balances, and history are all persisted there.

---

## Upgrading later

  - Add more leagues: edit LEAGUES array in server/index.js
  - Change starter balance: edit users table DEFAULT 100.00 in server/index.js
  - Settle bets automatically: add a cron job that checks finished fixtures
    and updates bet statuses (I can build this for you)
